      <scopecontent id="aspace_5d3f7673ca1f194a0b63bd8371106d74">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Edgar Howard Sturtevant Papers consist of incoming letters and drafts of a few outgoing letters. Many of the leading Hittite scholars are represented, but seldom by more than two or three items. The principal subjects are minor points of scholarship and routine academic business. The arrangement is alphabetical.</p>
         <p>These papers were the gift of F. W. Hopkins to Yale University in 1964.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_f0ccb8abfc1248205c067c9672a096c1">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Educator; B.A., U. of Indiana, 1898; Ph.D., U. of Chicago, 1891; joined the Yale faculty in 1923 as an assistant professor of Greek and Latin, became an associate professor in 1926 and a full professor in 1927, retired in 1943; one of the foremost authorities on the ancient Hittite language.</p>  
      </bioghist>
